codex
The branch was already largely in place, so I fixed the concrete spec mismatches I found instead of reworking the refactor blindly.

I updated [codex.integration.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/e2e/codex.integration.test.ts) so Codex-specific non-applicable steps are recorded with explicit reasons instead of being silently skipped, which matches the refactor plan. I also clarified the 34-interaction numbering in [exercise-flow.md](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/environments/lab-rat-todo-project/exercise-flow.md) and [ux-spec.md](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/environments/lab-rat-todo-project/ux-spec.md), and added a missing `typecheck` script to [packages/happy-server/package.json](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/package.json).

Verification: `happy-sync` unit and integration tests passed, `happy-server` build/typecheck passed, `happy-coder` build passed, `happy-app` typecheck plus targeted sync tests passed, and the Codex Level 2 file now loads cleanly. The real-agent Level 2/3 gates still depend on external credentials/runtime; in this environment the Codex E2E suite was skipped because those vars are not set.
